'm thinking about injuries related to that.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.078793,0.11398,0.11471,0.10408,0.094432,0.087454,0.084005,0.077184,0.071925,0.068161,0.058385,0.046885],"unified_progress":[0.067669,0.093252,0.095978,0.096559,0.093587,0.09467,0.090225,0.089816,0.081488,0.078349,0.065915,0.052492]},{"section":6,"text":"The pain is on the left side, so it's probably not a right-sided issue.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.070629,0.099516,0.098181,0.10078,0.089095,0.086608,0.086439,0.082288,0.078902,0.076549,0.071036,0.059973],"unified_progress":[0.067179,0.087993,0.087979,0.090267,0.090659,0.091863,0.089504,0.092589,0.086191,0.08417,0.073123,0.058483]},{"section":7,"text":"The areas affected are the lower chest, upper abdomen, and shoulder.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.059552,0.095111,0.094827,0.097472,0.090847,0.089194,0.089188,0.084255,0.079688,0.075788,0.073589,0.070488],"unified_progress":[0.061884,0.086845,0.087804,0.090637,0.090187,0.091944,0.088815,0.090159,0.087215,0.081202,0.075186,0.068124]},{"section":8,"text":"Lower chest pain could be related to the lungs or heart, maybe a contusion or something more serious like a fracture.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036242,0.069836,0.090342,0.10737,0.10042,0.098344,0.10119,0.094373,0.087432,0.089882,0.069668,0.054907],"unified_progress":[0.037133,0.073183,0.091565,0.10441,0.10125,0.098821,0.10181,0.097616,0.092064,0.085832,0.069214,0.047093]},{"section":9,"text":"Upper abdominal pain might involve the liver, spleen, or other organs.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041947,0.063993,0.081073,0.094171,0.098834,0.10118,0.10423,0.099197,0.092904,0.08995,0.073683,0.058835],"unified_progress":[0.043562,0.071006,0.086469,0.095638,0.1001,0.10023,0.10002,0.098166,0.093335,0.086818,0.071526,0.053133]},{"section":10,"text":"The shoulder pain suggests a possible fracture, maybe a clavicle fracture since that's a common injury in such accidents, especially in skiing where falls can happen.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042359,0.057444,0.074136,0.08473,0.094252,0.10027,0.10409,0.10504,0.10173,0.093977,0.078273,0.063696],"unified_progress":[0.045367,0.066897,0.083165,0.092045,0.097179,0.10418,0.10171,0.10001,0.094342,0.088193,0.072419,0.054505]},{"section":11,"text":"Putting this together, the mid torso hit against a tree could mean a collision that caused multiple injuries.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046996,0.069101,0.07558,0.080061,0.080913,0.083602,0.088345,0.089554,0.091144,0.096531,0.095703,0.10247],"unified_progress":[0.05008,0.069315,0.074606,0.081325,0.083655,0.088256,0.088407,0.092184,0.091146,0.090695,0.093422,0.09691]},{"section":12,"text":"The combination of lower chest and upper abdominal pain along with shoulder pain points towards a rib fracture.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047046,0.062147,0.066437,0.071973,0.071636,0.075293,0.079546,0.084152,0.089027,0.097146,0.11236,0.14324],"unified_progress":[0.04705,0.060867,0.064388,0.069545,0.072675,0.079684,0.080866,0.088724,0.092904,0.095493,0.11239,0.13541]},{"section":13,"text":"Specifically, the left side being hit might have caused a fracture in the ribs, which could be a rib fracture or maybe a more severe injury like a pulmonary contusion if the ribs are broken near the lungs.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038329,0.050155,0.066916,0.078111,0.087162,0.093891,0.099381,0.10327,0.10418,0.10168,0.092202,0.084724],"unified_progress":[0.041582,0.060376,0.076145,0.083977,0.089463,0.095978,0.096885,0.098872,0.09864,0.09563,0.087204,0.075247]},{"section":14,"text":"Wait, but she also has upper abdominal pain.","dimension":8,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035319,0.064507,0.069859,0.075357,0.081562,0.088937,0.094696,0.10241,0.10827,0.10689,0.09888,0.073322],"unified_progress":[0.040998,0.073715,0.084627,0.093521,0.094869,0.094573,0.097449,0.097511,0.093998,0.090694,0.077671,0.060374]},{"section":15,"text":"Could that be a sign of internal injury?","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042158,0.05732,0.07239,0.083034,0.088542,0.094086,0.099187,0.10197,0.10263,0.10308,0.088299,0.067304],"unified_progress":[0.049415,0.071297,0.08409,0.092902,0.095818,0.096094,0.098031,0.097746,0.093451,0.089871,0.075241,0.056044]},{"section":16,"text":"Maybe a spleen injury or something else, but the shoulder pain is more pointing towards a clavicle or rib issue.","dimension":8,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043339,0.047122,0.064454,0.075701,0.085806,0.094095,0.099923,0.10584,0.10836,0.10671,0.094933,0.073712],"unified_progress":[0.046544,0.063609,0.079417,0.089724,0.094567,0.096225,0.098323,0.098536,0.095939,0.092738,0.080371,0.064008]},{"section":17,"text":"Since the impact was on the mid torso, it's likely that the ribs are involved.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044183,0.055099,0.065801,0.072728,0.07914,0.085617,0.091374,0.096859,0.10075,0.10324,0.10252,0.10268],"unified_progress":[0.047819,0.064185,0.072953,0.080685,0.084804,0.089764,0.091187,0.094214,0.094393,0.093888,0.093402,0.092707]},{"section":18,"text":"So, the most probable diagnosis is a rib fracture, probably on the left side where the impact occurred.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028699,0.041584,0.052796,0.060844,0.066252,0.07224,0.078653,0.086916,0.095517,0.11004,0.13015,0.17631],"unified_progress":[0.027877,0.043432,0.054029,0.063854,0.068288,0.077558,0.081253,0.089557,0.097882,0.10362,0.12875,0.16391]},{"section":19,"text":"The patient's presentation suggests a rib fracture, specifically on the left side, given the impact from the skiing accident.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_