ait, there's something called the Kehr's sign.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.058058,0.12485,0.06184,0.099287,0.096385,0.098404,0.086906,0.084314,0.080955,0.076232,0.06892,0.063849],"unified_progress":[0.070662,0.10638,0.07164,0.098916,0.097869,0.101,0.087535,0.088373,0.08239,0.077129,0.067497,0.050602]},{"section":7,"text":"That's when a ruptured spleen causes left shoulder pain because the blood from the spleen irritates the phrenic nerve, which supplies the diaphragm.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.052359,0.090334,0.093349,0.094907,0.096428,0.096433,0.09433,0.089308,0.084679,0.078169,0.067373,0.06233],"unified_progress":[0.061326,0.073579,0.08937,0.10149,0.099978,0.10085,0.095912,0.092249,0.087076,0.076877,0.064901,0.056387]},{"section":8,"text":"The diaphragm is near the shoulder area through nerve pathways.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045844,0.084038,0.090617,0.095631,0.096168,0.096911,0.095266,0.090407,0.091052,0.079971,0.070347,0.063748],"unified_progress":[0.05543,0.073627,0.089582,0.099529,0.10394,0.10109,0.097637,0.092598,0.090229,0.077571,0.064262,0.054505]},{"section":9,"text":"So if she hit her left side, maybe the spleen was injured.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047011,0.083811,0.089769,0.095118,0.095274,0.096136,0.094188,0.089775,0.091405,0.081464,0.071129,0.06492],"unified_progress":[0.06505,0.076938,0.089124,0.098589,0.10191,0.097535,0.09571,0.091444,0.08896,0.075448,0.063537,0.055753]},{"section":10,"text":"The spleen is in the left upper quadrant, so a direct blow there could cause a splenic rupture.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04308,0.081557,0.089678,0.09625,0.096501,0.097559,0.095478,0.08993,0.093184,0.081181,0.070385,0.065218],"unified_progress":[0.054232,0.074093,0.090724,0.10062,0.10455,0.10231,0.098338,0.092369,0.09063,0.075236,0.06237,0.054533]},{"section":11,"text":"The abdominal pain in the upper abdomen and the shoulder pain align with that.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04094,0.080992,0.088244,0.092095,0.093033,0.094376,0.094219,0.091649,0.092173,0.085326,0.077332,0.06962],"unified_progress":[0.054862,0.075733,0.086371,0.094446,0.098978,0.097111,0.096153,0.093631,0.091369,0.082306,0.070029,0.059011]},{"section":12,"text":"Also, the mechanism of injury\u2014blunt trauma to the left chest or abdomen\u2014is classic for splenic injury.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040307,0.078785,0.0871,0.092602,0.094165,0.09711,0.095003,0.091642,0.092468,0.085916,0.075842,0.069059],"unified_progress":[0.055196,0.078774,0.088198,0.09594,0.098324,0.098035,0.095264,0.092477,0.090641,0.080037,0.068433,0.05868]},{"section":13,"text":"I should consider other possibilities too, like rib fractures or pulmonary issues, but the combination of abdominal and shoulder pain points more towards the spleen.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034413,0.075517,0.09434,0.099771,0.096679,0.09099,0.090952,0.087184,0.086743,0.091603,0.077109,0.074697],"unified_progress":[0.035477,0.066975,0.08103,0.093997,0.096926,0.09463,0.097445,0.094998,0.094054,0.096098,0.08084,0.067532]},{"section":14,"text":"Let me think if there's anything else.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.31513,0.051091,0.051288,0.060252,0.061625,0.064698,0.062061,0.070368,0.07156,0.067673,0.071424,0.052826],"unified_progress":[0.19996,0.077504,0.065411,0.064066,0.074771,0.07513,0.092518,0.084368,0.081407,0.065965,0.060951,0.057945]},{"section":15,"text":"Pancreatic injury?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029755,0.068209,0.061642,0.10162,0.10739,0.099755,0.10367,0.099513,0.094019,0.088113,0.080744,0.065571],"unified_progress":[0.042781,0.078616,0.070249,0.098387,0.10562,0.10129,0.099979,0.099233,0.092757,0.085366,0.072664,0.053053]},{"section":16,"text":"Maybe, but Kehr's sign is more spleen.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024,0.055985,0.071682,0.083207,0.092185,0.096836,0.10188,0.1018,0.10022,0.098398,0.091117,0.082694],"unified_progress":[0.032498,0.057036,0.073039,0.083933,0.091964,0.097772,0.098871,0.10087,0.099658,0.099996,0.089054,0.075313]},{"section":17,"text":"So the most likely diagnosis here is a ruptured spleen.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025784,0.051128,0.06065,0.067991,0.073857,0.07952,0.085369,0.089191,0.096891,0.09941,0.10841,0.1618],"unified_progress":[0.026497,0.038487,0.047994,0.0588,0.063846,0.074024,0.077578,0.087388,0.096475,0.10388,0.13806,0.18698]}]}}